00:00:58.640 --> 00:01:01.910
So in case you haven't kind have
gotten the quick Google+

00:01:01.910 --> 00:01:05.110
Sign-In overview, let me just
do that in about 30 seconds

00:01:05.110 --> 00:01:08.170
Google+ Sign-In is an
authentication option for

00:01:08.170 --> 00:01:10.210
websites, for applications.

00:01:10.210 --> 00:01:12.160
And what it's allowing you
to do is use your Google

00:01:12.160 --> 00:01:14.880
credentials to log
into websites.

00:01:14.880 --> 00:01:18.040
And it makes it much easier than
to have an application

00:01:18.040 --> 00:01:18.910
personalized.

00:01:18.910 --> 00:01:21.190
And this is sort of a trend
that's happening all

00:01:21.190 --> 00:01:24.050
throughout application now,
which is that you expect to

00:01:24.050 --> 00:01:28.090
have personalized or familiar
experiences within

00:01:28.090 --> 00:01:29.110
applications.

00:01:29.110 --> 00:01:31.120
And now Google is making
that very easy.

00:01:31.120 --> 00:01:34.350
And we also think that users
prefer Google in that

00:01:34.350 --> 00:01:34.710
environment.

00:01:34.710 --> 00:01:35.800
They trust Google.

00:01:35.800 --> 00:01:38.360
And it's a great choice
to put in front of

00:01:38.360 --> 00:01:40.530
users to enable that.

00:01:40.530 --> 00:01:43.680
And what we're doing with
Google+ Sign-In is that we are

00:01:43.680 --> 00:01:47.140
giving developers this choice
for authentication, but then

00:01:47.140 --> 00:01:49.150
we're also putting lots of
functionality underneath it

00:01:49.150 --> 00:01:50.840
that's additional value.

00:01:50.840 --> 00:01:53.535
So for example, and you might
have seen this example a

00:01:53.535 --> 00:01:54.520
couple of times.

00:01:54.520 --> 00:01:56.950
When you log in with Google
and if you own an Android

00:01:56.950 --> 00:01:59.850
device, we will then open up a
window that says, would you

00:01:59.850 --> 00:02:02.470
like to also download
the application?

00:02:02.470 --> 00:02:06.100
And so it turns out that 40% of
Android users that log in

00:02:06.100 --> 00:02:07.890
with Google then download
the app.

00:02:07.890 --> 00:02:09.039
So that's a big number.

00:02:09.039 --> 00:02:10.430
And so that's just an
example of the kind

00:02:10.430 --> 00:02:11.870
of thing we're doing.

00:02:11.870 --> 00:02:14.190
We announced yesterday that once
a user downloads the app,

00:02:14.190 --> 00:02:15.750
they're then automatically
logged in.

00:02:15.750 --> 00:02:17.940
So what Google will continue to
do over the course of the

00:02:17.940 --> 00:02:21.060
next several quarters is release
more and more cool

00:02:21.060 --> 00:02:24.800
things for developers, for
businesses, that can help them

00:02:24.800 --> 00:02:27.460
build a Google+ integration that
adds significant value.

